From 935164b2230101086bfff4701a4ca3b36564624b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 7 Nov 2025 11:30:38 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] AP MLD: Fix crash during link reconf response ack failure

When an ADD_LINK reconfiguration response is not ACKed by the STA, added links
must be reverted. The revert path in hostapd_link_reconf_resp_tx_status()
incorrectly iterates del_req instead of add_req, preventing proper cleanup and
potentially causing a crash.

Call trace:
 - hostapd_link_reconf_resp_tx_status
 - handle_action_cb
 - ieee802_11_mgmt_cb
 - mlme_event_mgmt_tx_status
 - do_process_drv_event
 - process_global_event
 - nl_recvmsgs ()

Fix this by iterating over req_list->add_req to remove added link STAs
on ack failure, and add a guard when add_req is empty to avoid
unnecessary work during cleanup.

Patch-work: [PATCH] AP MLD: Fix crash during link reconf response ack failure

Fixes: ea7af69a2369 ("AP MLD: Process TX status for Link Reconfiguration Response frame")
Signed-off-by: Govindaraj Saminathan <gsaminat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11_eht.c | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11_eht.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11_eht.c
@@ -1518,7 +1518,10 @@ void hostapd_link_reconf_resp_tx_status(
 		wpa_printf(MSG_INFO, "MLD: Link Reconf Response ack failed; "
 			   "revert link additions");
 
-		dl_list_for_each(info, &req_list->del_req,
+		if (!req_list->num_add_req)
+			goto exit;
+
+		dl_list_for_each(info, &req_list->add_req,
 				 struct link_reconf_req_info, list) {
 			if (info->status != WLAN_STATUS_SUCCESS)
 				continue;
